                            <comment id="412300" author="defazio" created="Tue, 23 Apr 2024 22:18:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is almost certainly a zfs issue and not lustre.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="412299" author="defazio" created="Tue, 23 Apr 2024 22:16:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adilger&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adilger&quot;&gt;adilger&lt;/a&gt; Yes, this likely a zfs issue. I&apos;ve talked with Brian Behlendorf and he thinks it&apos;s potentially similar to a bug that was recently fixed for zfs master. We&apos;ll pull in the patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/openzfs/zfs/pull/16049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/openzfs/zfs/pull/16049&lt;/a&gt; after we&apos;ve gotten to zfs 2.2.x, which should be soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="411764" author="adilger" created="Thu, 18 Apr 2024 17:29:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this is deep into the ZFS xattr lookup code, doing a lookup with a constant string into a buffer on the stack:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
dt_obj_version_t dt_version_get(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; struct lu_env *env, struct dt_object *o)
{
��������        struct lu_buf vbuf;
        ��������&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; *xname = XATTR_NAME_VERSION;
        ��������dt_obj_version_t version;
        ��������&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; rc;

��������        LASSERT(o);
��������        vbuf.lb_buf = &amp;amp;version;
        ��������vbuf.lb_len = sizeof(version);
        ��������rc = dt_xattr_get(env, o, &amp;amp;vbuf, xname);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Could this be an issue in the ZFS code?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="411761" author="defazio" created="Thu, 18 Apr 2024 16:55:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For my notes, the local ticket is TOSS-6269&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
